     {q:"Lithium-ion batteries are preferred for EVs because ___.", options:["they use no lithium","they are non-rechargeable","they are the cheapest batteries available","they have high energy density, low weight, and can be recharged many times — though mining lithium raises environmental and ethical concerns"], answer:3},
     {q:"The Downs cell uses electrolysis to produce ___.", options:["aluminium from bauxite","hydrogen from water","table salt from sodium and chlorine","sodium metal and chlorine gas from molten NaCl — allowing the production of pure sodium used in various industrial processes"], answer:3},
     {q:"Electroplating uses electrolysis to ___.", options:["dissolve metals","extract metals from ore","measure metal purity","coat an object with a thin layer of metal by making it the cathode in an electroplating solution containing the metal ions"], answer:3}
